            "answer_text": "Almost all the Arabs outside the Arabian peninsuela only call themselves Arabs because of the initial kharaj (a tax on land for non-Arabs) When the kharaj was introduced non-Arabs had to pay the tax even though they converted to Islam so they didn't have to pay the jizya anymore. The Umayyads/Abassids did this because they needed more money. So what did non-muslims do to not pay the kharaj? The same thing they did to not pay the jizya, they said they were Muslim and Arabs and eventually that identity stuck. The overwhelming majority of the people living in these areas are the same people of the past obviously, they did what they did to go around paying taxes. ",
